  "description": "Bounded promotion proof for the unistd_abi GNU stack protector row and the LFS alias rows that already have strict and hardened ABI evidence.",
  "rationale": "The promoted rows cover the GNU stack protector abort contract plus LP64 LFS alias contracts for ftruncate64, lseek64, mmap64, pread64, pwrite64, sendfile64, and truncate64. __stack_chk_fail is cataloged in the support matrix under unistd_abi but implemented in fortify_abi; its fixture proof binds the abort behavior while the host-delegation census hits are abort, libio exit-safety, errno, and signal-mask helper artifacts. The LFS symbols alias FrankenLibC's native syscall, mmap, and I/O paths; their census hits are errno/bootstrap helpers plus alias reachability to the native non-64 entrypoints, not host-glibc semantic call-through.",
